SP  - 1079
EP  - 1097
VL  - 66
IS  - 3
KW  - labor share
KW  - market power
KW  - optimal capital taxation
KW  - profit share
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12766
Y2  - 2026/04/24
N2  - ABSTRACT We analyze the implications of the decline in labor's share in national income for optimal Ramsey taxation. It is optimal to accompany the decline in labor share by raising capital taxes only if the labor share is falling because of a decline in competition or other mechanisms that raise the share of pure profits. This result holds under various alternative institutional arrangements that are relevant for optimal taxation of capital income. A quantitative application to the US economy shows that soaring profit shares since the 1980s can justify a significantly increasing path of capital income taxes.
ER  - 

