VL  - 66
IS  - 3
KW  - buffer stock model
KW  - consumption
KW  - debt aversion
KW  - experimental economics
KW  - income variance
KW  - intertemporal optimization
KW  - liquidity constraints
KW  - savings
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12784
Y2  - 2026/04/24
N2  - ABSTRACT We test the buffer stock model of savings behavior using a three-period intertemporal model. In one treatment, liquidity in the second period is constrained (borrowing not possible), while the unconstrained treatment has no such constraint. The buffer stock model predicts that a second-period liquidity constraint increases first-period savings. We also vary the variance of stochastic income (high or low) in a $2 \times 2$ design. While we find no evidence for the predicted liquidity constraint effect, most other predictions hold, for example, income variance effects. Observed departures can be explained by some combination of debt aversion, cognitive heterogeneity, and/or learning.
ER  - 
